The minimal all-features shape is converging on an alt-b-specific shared-internals ABI, not the current generic public React API. That removes the entire isomorphic façade and seven export shims. The irreducible core is much smaller: lane/batch tenancy, pass start plus “rendering now,” per-root commit/retirement, and same-lane corrective scheduling. Yield/resume, mutation brackets, discard-all-WIP, generations, and test reset are not behavior-bearing for alt-b.
