   445	
   446	### Prototype exit rule
   447	
   448	Do not add userspace receipts, K1, lock views, evaluator chains, or validity
   449	stamps to rescue a failed fork spike. If detached queues or dependency
   450	lifetime cannot pass the nine fork invariants directly, reject ROOT-CELL and
   220	### M3. Fiber leaf dependencies
   221	
   222	`readRootCell(cell)` does three things:
   223	
   224	1. returns the pass's M2 snapshot value;
   225	2. appends an internal `CellDependency` to the currently rendering Fiber's
   226	   work-in-progress dependency list;
   227	3. examines the cell's base/pending queues and schedules this Fiber in every
   228	   lane not represented by this pass, including post-pin operations.
   229	
   230	The cell also links the dependency into an intrusive reverse list. A write:
   231	
   232	- requests its lane once;
   233	- schedules every committed consumer;
   234	- schedules every consumer in an open pass that already read the cell;
   235	- always marks root-cell work in that lane, even with no consumers.
   236	
   237	There is no delivery equality cutoff or cross-write suppression. React may
   238	coalesce multiple markings of the same Fiber/lane.
   239	
   240	At commit, work-in-progress cell dependencies replace the rendered Fibers'
   241	current dependencies. At pass discard, they are unlinked. Dependencies from
   242	Fibers that did not render remain current. Dependency records are pooled, but
   243	pooling is an optimization and not part of correctness.
   244	
   245	Committed dependency changes also call the cell's library-owned observed-count
   246	callback. K0 subscribers and committed Fiber consumers contribute to one Atom
   247	count; the Atom's 0→1 setup and 1→0 cleanup remain microtask-damped. WIP reads
   248	do not count as observation until they commit.
   249	
   250	This deliberately follows React Context's lifetime rather than inventing a
   251	library adoption protocol: current React resets the work-in-progress context
   252	dependency list before a render, records reads on the rendering Fiber, and
   253	marks matching consumer lanes and their ancestor paths on propagation. A root
   254	cell needs a keyed reverse list instead of Context's tree scan, but the
   255	current/work-in-progress ownership rule is the same.
   256	
   257	### M4. Pass-local computed evaluation
   258	
   259	A pass owns scratch storage keyed by immutable global `Computed` identity.
   260	Each entry is `{ value | error | thenable, leaves }`. `leaves` is the deduped
   261	list of root cells read by the evaluation, including nested computeds.
   262	
   263	- Cache miss: evaluate against M2, directly accumulating leaves.
   264	- Cache hit: return the cached outcome and replay every leaf through M3 for
   265	  the current Fiber.
   266	- Pass end/discard: clear the scratch in O(entries) and reuse its arrays.
   267	
   268	`useComputed(fn, deps)` is different: it is an ordinary hook-local render
   269	calculation and returns `T`, not `Computed<T>`. React already versions its
   270	closure with the Fiber. Its signal reads go through M3.

