   326	## 6. Public API semantics
   327	
   328	```ts
   329	new Atom<T>({ state, effect?, isEqual?, label? })
   330	new Computed<T>({ fn, isEqual?, label? }) // fn immutable
   331	new ReducerAtom<S, A>({ state, reducer, isEqual?, label? }) // reducer immutable
   332	
   333	atom.state
   334	atom.set(value)
   335	atom.update(pureOperation)
   336	reducerAtom.dispatch(action)
   337	
   338	useSignal(signal): T
   339	useComputed(fn, deps): T
   340	```
   341	
   342	`useSignal` and `useComputed` retain their last committed result in ordinary
   343	hook state. `isEqual(next, committed)` may select the committed reference for
   344	the hook result. Computed functions must treat `isEqual` values as semantically
   345	interchangeable; there is no shared React-world computed cache.
   346	
   347	`batch()` delays core-effect flushing only. It never delays M3 delivery,
   348	so a transition nested inside `batch()` keeps its own lane. `untracked()`
   349	suppresses dependency recording but still reads the current context's value:
   350	M2 during render/effect, K0 otherwise.
   351	
   352	A stable thenable passed to `ctx.use` delegates to React `use` in render. In
   353	core evaluation it is cached as the computed's thrown outcome. Resource
   354	creation/caching is an application concern in v1.
